HEADWORD: Laminiplantar
<hw>Lam`i*ni*plan"tar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Lamina</ets> + L. <ets>planta</ets> sole of the foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the tarsus covered behind with a horny
sheath continuous on both sides, as in most singing birds, except the
larks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laminitis</ent>⟦br⟧
